cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SI, cs.PF 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with the mean user throughput in cellular networks. It could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it uses Little's law to express the mean user throughput. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) as it deals with the spatial distribution of the SINR. It could also be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with network irregularities and shadowing. Finally, it could belong to cs.PF (Performance) as it deals with the performance of cellular networks.
